div.div:
I, the protagonist, was just an ordinary high school girl, but suddenly I was reincarnated as a spider monster in a fantasy world. Not only that, but I awakened in a dungeon filled with vicious monsters. Armed with only my human knowledge and my overwhelming positivity, I'm forced to use spiderwebs and traps to defeat far stronger monsters just to stay alive... So begins the labyrinth survival story of a girl with incredible mental strength living as one of the lowest-ranked beasts!
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka IV: Shin Shou Meikyuu-hen

The fourth season of Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka. Intrepid adventurer Bell Cranel has leveled up, but he can’t rest on his dungeoneering laurels just yet. The Hestia Familia still has a long way to go before it can stand toe-to-toe with the other Familias of Orario — but before Bell can set out on his next mission, reports of a brutal murder rock the adventuring community! One of Bell’s trusted allies stands accused of the horrible crime, and it’s up to Bell and his friends to clear their name and uncover a nefarious plot brewing in the dungeon’s dark depths. (Source: Sentai Filmworks)

Yui was reincarnated into the noble Nuir family. When it appears that she failed to inherit her family’s enchanted tailoring gifts, the seamstress is in for a life of misfortune. Will meeting a kind noble be enough to change her fate?
(Source: Yen Press)

Iruma Suzuki has always been eager to please, even at the cost of his well-being. Worst yet, he's the son of two selfish parents who end up selling him to a demon. Thanks to their totally irresponsible actions, Iruma has found himself living in the Netherworld, where he must live and attend school as the grandson of an older demon. Luckily, his new, doting grandfather is there to help, but Iruma will have to figure out how to blend in with his demonic classmates or risk getting eaten. All he needs to do is subjugate rival classmates, summon familiars, and do other typical demon things while never revealing that he's human… Piece of cake, right?

div.span: Turbulent Adventurers are Introverted, Observant, Feeling, Prospecting and Turbulent. They tend to have open minds, approaching life, new experiences, and people with grounded warmth.
Likely prefers fewer, yet deep and meaningful, social interactions and feels drawn to calmer environments.
Likely pragmatic and down-to-earth, with a strong focus on what is happening or very likely to happen.
Likely values emotional expression and sensitivity, prioritizing empathy, social harmony, and cooperation.
Likely very good at improvising and adapting. Tends to be flexible and values novelty above stability.
Likely self-conscious, sensitive to stress, success-driven, perfectionistic, and eager to improve.
